 I hope people realize with the NASA contract that is just for a prototype which passed testing yesterday I think.  There is an article on that out there.  I know people think the Secret Space Program is a fantasy but it really isn't.  The Pentagon for decades has lost trillions off their budgets.  That money was not "lost" and it was not "accounting errors".  It was going to fund advanced technology.  What Trump did with creating a Space Force was to provide a vehicle for the Pentagon to start bringing some of that technology out.   Remember, to keep an advanced tech secret they cannot go through Congress.  So they need a mechanism to legitimize expenditures.  The fact that Nokia is on the ground floor is telling and that prototype could lead to significant downstream contracts or a major acquisition of Bell Labs or variations of these types of things.  People that think Trump is an idiot are complete and utter fools.  That man is more brilliant than you think or he appears.

$NOK CEO Lundmark appears specifically concerned about Mobile Networks: “Competitive intensity, which is particularly impacting Mobile Access and is expected to continue at a high level in full year 2020, as some competitors seek to take share in the early stage of 5G.” His comment “win 5G whatever it takes ... in areas we choose to compete” could mean putting a lot of money in to trying to catch up against intense competition in this area. Or he could pick his battles and sell this underperforming department. Doing so would resolve the VZ/Samsung thorn in his side, and could be a win-win situation with a buyer like the US government.
